        "text": "The snake grows every move with no food. This isn't Snake — it's a self-avoiding walk on a bounded grid. The game is the Hamiltonian path problem: visit every cell exactly once starting from (5,5).\n\nHamiltonian paths on grid graphs always exist for n×m where n,m ≥ 2. The zigza...",
